s a new analytic model of transnational advocacy. In investigating advocacy around a critical economic and social right—the right to food—Jurkovich challenges existing understandings of the relationships among human rights, norms, and laws. Most important, Feeding the Hungry provides an expanded conceptual tool kit with which we can examine and understand the social and moral forces at play in rights advocacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFood reliefxInternational cooperation. 0aFood reliefxPolitical aspects. 0aFood securityxPolitical aspects. 0aHungerxPolitical aspects. 0aHungerxPreventionxInternational cooperation. 0aRight to food. 4aHumanities & Human Rights. 4aInternational Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy (see also SOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food) .2bisacsh  aNGO, Sustainable Development Goals, Food Security, Economic Rights, Social Rights, Development, Agriculture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501751189?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501751189423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501751189/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-0704